sense.examples: How misdirected are the arguments that life does not begin at conception. So it reminds you of how misdirected the activity is. There's nothing misdirected about Xobni. But the government is misdirected. Arguably, some of these laws were even misdirected to begin with.

sense.name: to lead in the wrong direction or to direct to the wrong spot.
sense.examples: The pedestrian misdirected the out-of-town driver. Next thing you know, your PC is misdirected to a phishing page. Previous attempts to understand TB diversity have been misdirected. Mrs. Sheehan's anger is misdirected. But it resemble the Greek letter pi, and that's what misdirected me. Anger is misdirected when you're grieving, by definition. Iran misdirected attention to a controversial reactor at Bushehr. Conservatives counter that liberals have misdirected their compassion.
